quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,82,"So when Our command came, We made the highest part [of the city] its lowest and rained upon them stones of layered hard clay, [which were]"
  11,83,"Marked from your Lord. And it [i.e., Allāh's punishment] is not from the wrongdoers [very] far."
  11,84,"And to Madyan [We sent] their brother Shuʿayb. He said, "
  12,43,"And [subsequently] the king said, "
  12,44,"They said, "
  12,45,"But the one who was freed and remembered after a time said, "
  13,10,"It is the same [to Him] concerning you whether one conceals [his] speech or publicizes it and whether one is hidden by night or conspicuous [among others] by day."
  13,11,"For him [i.e., each one] are successive [angels]{1} before and behind him who protect him by the decree of Allāh.{2} Indeed, Allāh will not change the condition of a people until they change what is in themselves. And when Allāh intends for a people ill,{3} there is no repelling it. And there is not for them besides Him any patron.",footnotes:1:Replacing each other by turn.,footnotes:2:The phrase may also be rendered \"...who guard him from [everything except] the decree of Allāh.\",footnotes:3:i.e., punishment or destruction because of their sins.
  13,12,"It is He who shows you lightning, [causing] fear and aspiration, and generates the heavy clouds."